sentences: The Furies are a five-piece indie band from Providence, Rhode Island, that formed in 2010.
Moretti released her first song "Keep Away" in 2011, which features Brad Hargreaves on drums, Abe Millet on bass and Stephan Jenkins on tambourine.
Their first performance was a record release show at the Boston Hard Rock Cafe, on April 9, 2011.

In 2014, the Furies released the single "Hunter," described by Telegram & Gazette as a "beautiful, sexy and wholly immersive song, one thatâ€™s devoid of sentimentality and that captures this all-consuming sort of heartbreak with frightening alacrity."
The song appears on the six-track EP, Omens, which was released on November 13, 2015.
They won the 2018 New England Music Award for Best in State Rhode Island.
Omens was digitally reissued with Mint 400 Records, on March 5, 2019.
They are currently recording an album, scheduled for release in 2021.

A 2015 piece by Tyler Pearce of City Newspaper, describes the Furies music as "rock guitars [with] weighted body, while snare and hi-hat give texture and groove to a beautiful vocal-forward sound with lush harmonies."
That year the Furies toured across the United States.
The Furies have shared the stage with the Ataris, Big Scary, Howie Day, the Indigo Girls, Joan Baez, and Mary Chapin Carpenter.
They are currently recording an album, scheduled for release in 2021.
